\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line The SAE Institute is registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training \'28until 31 December 2021\'29 as a private higher education institution under the name\'2C The SAE Institute of South Africa \'28Pty\'29 Ltd \'28DHET\'2C 17 March 2020\'29. The Institution has programmes accredited by the CHE.\line \line The Institution is currently applying for accreditation of the Bachelor of Arts in Motion Design and Animation which will be offered in the distance mode of delivery at the Cape Town Main Campus situated at Unit A307\'2C Woodstock Exchange\'2C 66 Albert Road\'2C Woodstock. The Institution currently only provides contact learning.\line \line The Institution has also applied for accreditation of the following nine programmes \'E2\'80\'93 in distance mode of delivery - which are in process\'3A\line - Higher Certificate in Sound Production\line - Higher Certificate in Game Design and Production\line - Higher Certificate in Animation and Visual Effects\line - Higher Certificate in Digital Film Production \line - Bachelor of Arts in Sound Production\line - Bachelor of Arts in Game Design and Production\line - Bachelor of Arts in Film Production\line - Higher Certificate in Music Production\line - Higher Certificate in Graphic Design.\line \line The Institution may offer the following eight registered qualifications in the contact mode of delivery \'28DHET\'2C 17 March 2020\'29\'3A\line - Higher Certificate in Sound Production\line - Higher Certificate in Game Design and Production\line - Higher Certificate in Animation and Visual Effects\line - Higher Certificate in Digital Film Production\line - Bachelor of Arts in Sound Production\line - Bachelor of Arts in Film Production\line - Bachelor of Arts in Motion Design and Animation \'28same title as current application\'29\line - Bachelor of Arts in Game Design and Production.\line \line The CHE\'E2\'80\'99s last visit to the Cape Town site of delivery was conducted on 20 July 2015. The site visit was linked to the relocation of programmes to the current registered site at the Woodstock Exchange \'28CHE letter\'2C 12 June 2015\'29. \line \line The long-term condition of a site visit is outstanding for the extension of six programmes to the \'27new\'27 additional site in Johannesburg \'28CHE letter\'2C 8 February 2019\'29.\line \line In November 2019\'2C the Institution applied for the extension of two programmes to the Johannesburg site\'2C namely the Higher Certificate in Game Design and Production and Bachelor of Arts in Game Design and Production. Both programmes were recently fully accredited after conditions were met \'28CHE letters\'2C 1 March 2019 \'26 1 August 2019\'29. \line \line The Higher Certificate in Virtual Reality Studies was recently accredited with one short-term condition \'28CHE letter\'2C 12 November 2019\'3B revised 14 November 2019\'29. The condition was met \'28CHE letter\'2C 29 June 2020\'29.\cell \pard 

